column5: Has anyone just returned from Lac Seul, I was wondering if the Lake has come up much.We'll be leaving Friday for BlackBay Outpost,Thanks. Catch and Release the Big Ones so somebody else has a chance to catch there DREAM FISH.
Levels are still very low, several feet below normal. A nominal rise has occurred since the start of the year (couple feet).
NWO Fishing Bum Thanks for the info Catch and Release the Big Ones so somebody else has a chance to catch there DREAM FISH.

I JUST RETURNED ON THE 19TH. LAKE LEVELS ARE ALMOST 5 FEET BELOW NORMAL. WEED GROWTH IS BEHIND DUE TO THE LOW LEVELS. THE CURRENT CONDITION HAS EXPOSED ALOT OF ROCK REEFS THAT ARE NORMALLY AT A SAFE DEPTH BY THIS TIME OF THE YEAR. WATCH YOUR PROP. HAVE A GREAT TRIP.

Just got back 7/19. The lake looked at least 7 feet down from last year. Many large docks are still totally out of the water. Kinda cool going to the old hot spots and seeing with my eyes what only my mind could imagine last year. Hmmm, shoulda picked up a few snagged rigs. Weedlines are generally undeveloped. I believe the fish are still trying to get into a pattern. Some shallow, some deep. Caught large and small fish together.
